data.description: End of season deal, be all set and ready for next year's swimming and boating season. Home is in move in condition with plenty of time to add your own touches. Large back yard for warm weather gatherings and fun BBQs and evenings around the fire pit. A shed to store your out of season toys.  Walk to the lake's beach to catch the captivating sunsets on the water. Enjoy the beautiful sunrises from the kitchen and main bedrooms large windows. Year round, rural setting with lake rights to Yankee Lake. A rare opportunity below 300k. Owners have relocated and anxious for offers. The home was built in 1981 and renovated in 2017, and current owners added some nice conveniences as well. The laundry area is in the hall near the bedrooms making it handy but out of the way. Bath has deep tub, modern lighting that can change colors, play music and use the fan, home is wired for alarm system.  Fish, swim, kayak, rowboat, canoe, paddle boat or paddle board, always something to do on the water. No motorboats for a peaceful, relaxing summer. A pellet stove in the living room keeps the house nice and toasty and saves money on the heat bills, The kitchen has real maple butcherblock counters and subway tile backsplash. 2 bedrooms and 1 bath. Electric panel box is wired for a generator, Horseshoe driveway makes it easy when more than one car.   Electric motors only. Annual $350.00 Membership includes use of the clubhouse and planned summer activities.  Lot is .46 acre and is approx. 98 x 198
